{"posts":[{"slug":"airbnb-icons-the-colosseum","id":"69a0721026045300011b3d76","uuid":"e9dae9c0-4e8b-4d75-9f1a-54ca5efbade0","title":"Airbnb Icons: The Colosseum","html":"<figure class=\"kg-card kg-embed-card\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/1038223261?h=051192e6e5&amp;app_id=122963\" width=\"426\" height=\"240\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" title=\"AirBnb Icons: The Colosseum\"></iframe></figure><p>We travelled to Rome to deliver <strong>Airbnb Icons: The Colosseum</strong> — a once-in-a-lifetime production inside one of the most iconic landmarks in the world. Filming in the real Colosseum brought a scale and atmosphere you simply can’t replicate. From sweeping drone shots over ancient stone to gladiators stepping into the arena, every frame carried the weight of history.</p><p>Working alongside <strong>Toy and Robin</strong>, who led the set design, we provided full camera services and lighting for the shoot. The challenge was balancing cinematic ambition with the realities of filming in a protected historic site. Every movement, setup and lighting decision had to respect the space while still delivering a bold, immersive visual experience.</p><p>The result is a piece that feels epic in scale and authentic in texture — a modern production set against a 2,000-year-old backdrop. Not a studio recreation. The real arena. The real Colosseum.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card kg-width-wide\"><img src=\"https://www.colmmoore.com/tinyark/content/images/2026/02/image-59.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" srcset=\"https://www.colmmoore.com/tinyark/content/images/size/w600/2026/02/image-59.png 600w, https://www.colmmoore.com/tinyark/content/images/size/w1000/2026/02/image-59.png 1000w, https://www.colmmoore.com/tinyark/content/images/size/w1600/2026/02/image-59.png 1600w, ht